Text processing in C can be tricky when parsing complex documents (like CSV files or configuration scripts).

**`fscanf()` and `sscanf()`**
While `fgets` reads whole lines safely, `fscanf(fptr, "%s %d", name, &age)` can be used to extract highly specific formatted data from a file.
Additionally, `sscanf` (String Scan) takes a string you ALREADY extracted, and parses it for formatted tokens!
```c
char data[] = "Hero 100";
char name[20];
int hp;
sscanf(data, "%s %d", name, &hp);
```
However, you must be terrified of buffer overflows when using `%s`. Always use limits: `%19s` forces `sscanf` to stop reading before crashing your 20-character array.
